history.content: I was actually talking to my friend who did this earlier. Apparently it’s actually easier. The hws are weekly just like the semester 189 and are of comparable difficulty but the exams were apparently easier since they didn’t go really in depth for some of the courses. Also my friend said they only had one midterm and a final and each were about an hour as compared to the normal semester with two 1.5 hr midterms and a 3 hr final.

We hardly ever know what upper divs we will be able to offer in summer session until January or sometimes even February because our graduate students (who generally teach these courses) haven't yet been organized by the faculty to accept positions to teach until close to that time.

I noticed that CS189 was offered during the summer session 2018.

Will CS189 be offered for the next summer session(summer session 2019) as well?

Also, CS189's workload is already high enough during the regular semester. Can someone who took the course this summer share some experience about taking 189 during the summer session?
history.subject: CS189 for the Summer Session
